    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="347"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/5–649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-06">May 6,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received May 6—4:13 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 331. Reuter despatch, datelined Canton May 5, states letter Li to
                    Generalissimo brought back from Kweilin by Li Wen-fan<note n="86"
                        xml:id="d347fn86">Former Vice President of the Chinese Judicial Yuan.</note>
                    contains following terms: <pb facs="0305" n="295" xml:id="pg_295"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Economically, all national property including gold, silver bars and
                            foreign currency transferred Taiwan 2 months ago be placed disposal of
                            Li.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Politically, government organs Canton go under control of Li.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Militarily, all troops Central [and] South China go under command of
                            Li.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Department Cantel 331, Nanking 253, Shanghai 211.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
